It's entirely possible you have a bad component someplace in there...do you have probs when doing anything else memory/cpu/graphics intensive (ie other games)?<br>
<br>
As for DAoC, there are always some issues with hw but most are solved with the usual &quot;update your drivers&quot; answer. It works on my work laptop, a p3-800 with 384mb and POS ATI Rage crap video. (Again, it's laggy as hell...maybe 10-15 fps, but it does run.) However, I will counterpoint that statement with a warning that DAoC does not have anywhere near the content of EQ -- you will be on a levelling treadmill to go [get sniped by archers and mages in] RvR. I still have my beta account for DA but really have not had much desire to play it since I got back to a real computer.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 coppers...good luck finding the prob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uzenak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tinkerbell</span><br>  Posts: 450<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/02 10:54:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2485.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What hardware do you run EQ on that works?  </span><hr size=1> Yuck, I must not have read that all the way through the first time.  Freezing after 30 mins sounds like it could be one of three things:<br>
<br>
1) Overheating  (CPU or Video Card)  Check all your fans, check the boards CPU temp sensor, maybe buy a Blue Orb for the video card.<br>
<br>
2) Memory issue: Check to make sure you have enough free drive space for a decent swap file, (~1.5 or 2 x your RAM). Download and run DocMem from <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.simmtester.com">www.simmtester.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> .  <br>
<br>
3) Power supply.  If you have more then one Hard drive unplug all but the boot drive, unplug all CD Drives and boot up, now try everquest.<br>
<br>
I guess it could be a few more things, but these are the three that jumped out at me first....<br>
<br>
